<br>
It's tough to hear that a bard who doesn't have both scales yet, somehow has the trak guts.  It's tough to see that they guts are on sale for MQ (although at least one person offered them for an EXTREMELY reasonable price).  It SUCKS to hear that the guts rotted.  So I sympathize with what you are saying, since, no doubt, the cleric epic is headed in this direction. (cept it can't be MQ'd, so needy clerics would have to be there at the time of the slaying)<br>
<br>
However, no matter that the clerics may prefer to have it the old way, about the cleric's GUILD, who had to bear the burden of the camp?  Guaranteed, they are MUCH better off.  <br>
<br>
If you argue otherwise, you must never have sat through an RF camp.  To do an RF camp literally meant putting the entire guild on hold from other raids/things (and even from RL stuff) for 1-4 days, and sometimes longer.  Everyone is needed to pitch in to do long shifts, cover late hours, and even take off work or lose sleep to hold the camp.<br>
<br>
Plus there is the added bonus of no longer worrying about hosting a Naggy raid (esp if Naggy spawned in the *middle* of your RF camp...).  Many RF-ready guilds (who could handle Chardok king) have members who are too high lvl to participate in Naggy raids, and don't enough twinks to be able to pull one of.  You ever run a public Naggy raid?<br>
<br>
(btw, FG respawn time is 6 hours 40 min, and the old RF could actually take up to 80 hours to spawn, provided there wasn't a patch, or Naggy didn't pop on top of him and kill him, or the zone didn't go down for whatever lame reason...) <p><TABLE style=filter:glow(color=green, 
